                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-04-06</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is one of the best biographies I have ever read. It is beautifully researched and written. It really is more than just a biography of Kruschev but a history of Russia from the 1920's to the 1960's, as well as of the Cold War. The depiction of Kremlin infighting, as well as the portrait if provides of Stalin, are first-rate. You will not regret reading this book.</span>
                  
              
